Minority Powerbrokers Q&A: Veyance's April Miller Boise



        ¬†    


					Law360, New York (November 17, 2014, 11:08 AM EST) -- April Miller Boise is general counsel and corporate secretary of Veyance Technologies Inc. (formerly Goodyear Engineered Products), a global industrial manufacturing company that recently agreed to sell its business to Continental AG. Prior to joining Veyance, Boise was the managing partner of Thompson Hine LLP‚Äôs Cleveland, Ohio, office and served on the firm‚Äôs executive committee. She has practiced law for more than 20 years. In private practice her work was focused primarily on advising clients on mergers and acquisitions, related securities matters and corporate governance....
				
