April Miller Boise: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 4:53 PM ET
Machinery

Company Overview of Meritor, Inc.



SnapshotPeople¬†




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
April Miller Boise  Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Corporate Secretary, Meritor, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 5 different industries.48--
Background

		Ms. April Miller Boise has been Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Corporate Secretary of Meritor, Inc. since August 15, 2016. Ms. Boise served as the Head of Global Mergers & Acquisitions, Senior Vice President, General Counsel and Secretary at AVINTIV Inc. since March 2015 and also served as its Chief Compliance Officer. She was responsible for the legal affairs of the AVINTIV Inc. Ms. Boise leads the AVINTIV's mergers and acquisitions efforts. Ms. Boise served ... as General Counsel, Senior Vice President, Head of Global Mergers & Acquisitions and Secretary at Avintiv Specialty Materials Inc. She served as Vice President, General Counsel, Chief Privacy Officer and Corporate Secretary of Veyance Technologies, Inc. since January 2011. She served as a Partner in Corporate Transactions & Securities practice group at Thompson Hine LLP. She served as a Corporate Attorney for Cleary, Gottlieb, Steen & Hamilton LLP, Husch & Eppenberger and Blackwell Sanders LLP and was a Labor Relations Associate at Ford Motor Co. Ms. Boise has more than 20 years of experience advising executive leaders in public and private companies on corporate governance, mergers, acquisitions, joint ventures and capital market transactions. She works efficiently as part of a team with in-house counsel in resolving clients' most challenging legal issues. Her practice includes mergers, acquisitions and joint ventures; securities offerings for public and private companies; private equity and venture capital; and corporate governance including Sarbanes-Oxley compliance. She served as Director of BioEnterprise Corporation until August 17, 2015. She is a Member of Board of Trustees at The Cleveland Foodbank, Inc. since 2000; Cuyahoga Community College Foundation since 2005 and Cleveland Zoological Society since 2003. She served as a Member of Board of Trustees at United Black Fund from 2000 to 2005. She holds JD from The University of Chicago Law School in 1994 and BBA from University of Michigan in 1990.Read Full Background




